approve: (1) full recovery of the costs of providing utility service, or (2) full recovery of all amounts invested in the utility business
and a reasonable return on those investments.
We identified the impact of rate regulation as a critical audit matter due to the significant judgments made by management to
support its assertions about impacted account balances and disclosures (e.g., asset retirement costs, property damage reserves, and
remaining net book values of retired assets) and the high degree of subjectivity involved in assessing the potential impact of future
