9. LEASES
Lessee
The Registrants recognize leases with a term of greater than 12 months on the balance sheet as lease obligations, representing the
discounted future fixed payments due, along with ROU assets that will be amortized over the term of each lease.
As lessee, the Registrants lease certain electric generating units (including renewable energy facilities), real estate/land,
communication towers, railcars, and other equipment and vehicles. The major categories of lease obligations are as follows:
